route 502 (also known as silver lane, the eastern connector, and the western connector) is a state highway in the u.s. state of connecticut. the highway connects the city of hartford with the town of simsbury, via the towns of east windsor and west windsor. route 502 begins at an interchange with i-91 in hartford, and proceeds eastward as silver lane through the city's downtown district. the highway intersects interstate 84 (the lindsay expressway) just west of downtown hartford, and proceeds into east windsor. in east windsor, route 502 intersects us 6 (main street) and crosses the farmington river into
quaero (latin for i seek) was a media platform that aimed to make information and knowledge more accessible to the public. it was founded in 2006 by nancy dubuc and stephane roy. in 2006, nancy dubuc and stephane roy founded quaero, an online information and knowledge platform. the site aimed to make information and knowledge more accessible to the public by aggregating content from a variety of sources and making it available in an easy-to-use format. quaero also offered tools for users to research specific topics, share content, and connect with others who were interested in the same topics. quaero
golda ginsburg krolik (born august 24, 1892) was a polish-born american attorney and politician. she served as the first female judge on the united states district court for the southern district of new york, from 1949 to 1963. golda krolik was born in 1892 in warsaw, poland. she studied law at the university of warsaw and the university of berlin. after completing her legal education, krolik moved to the united states in 1923. she began her career as an attorney in new york city. in 1939, krolik was appointed as a judge on the new york county court. in 1949,
carole ward allen is an american politician, who served as the 66th lieutenant governor of new york from 1983 to 1987. born in the bronx, allen received her b.a. from the university of rochester in 1969 and her j.d. from syracuse university college of law in 1973. she was a trial lawyer for several years before entering politics. allen was first elected to the new york state assembly in 1974, serving until 1978. she was then elected to the new york state senate, serving from 1979 until 1983, when she was appointed lieutenant governor by governor mario cuomo. allen was
beechdean motorsport (formerly beechdean mansell motorsport) is a british motor racing team that competes in the gp2 series. the team is owned and operated by beechdean racing, a british racing organisation which also owns the beechdean motorsport brand. the team was founded by former formula one driver nigel mansell and is currently managed by patrick friesacher. formed in 2009, beechdean motorsport made its debut in the gp2 series the following year with driver tom dillmann. the team has since competed in every season of the series, with dillmann as its only driver. in 2016, beechdean motorsport announced that it had
philip lawton (born 7 october 1977) is an english actor. he is known for his roles as dci john barnaby in the itv police drama barnaby, and as tom riddle in the harry potter films. philip lawton was born on 7 october 1977 in london, england. he is the son of actress faye dunaway and actor peter lawton. he has two sisters, actress elle fanning and actress dakota fanning. philip first started acting at the age of eight, appearing in a small role in the film the mystery of edwin drood. he went on to study at the royal academy
of dramatic art (rada), where he was awarded a bfa in 1998. after graduation from rada, philip appeared in a number of stage productions before landing his breakthrough role as dci john barnaby in the itv police drama barnaby. the show ran for four seasons from 2003 to 2007, and philip was nominated for a bafta tv award for best actor for his performance in 2006. since leaving barnaby, philip has starred in a number of projects, including the bbc period drama series call the midwife, alongside jennifer saunders and catherine tate, and the crime thriller the hollow crown, alongside
satyan "sam" pitroda (born 4 may 1946) is an indian-born american business executive. he is the former vice chairman and chief operating officer (coo) of verizon communications and a former executive chairman of pepsico. pitroda is also a distinguished fellow at the institute of telecommunication management and research, india's top telecom think-tank. pitroda was born in amritsar, punjab, india, to parents who were civil servants. he attended the government college, amritsar, where he participated in student politics and received a bachelor of science degree in economics in 1967. he then attended stanford university, where he received a master of business
administration degree in 1971. pitroda began his career with pepsico in 1971 as a financial analyst. he was promoted to controller in 1981 and then to senior vice president and coo in 1991. during his tenure at pepsico, pitroda was responsible for worldwide operations and led the company's turnaround efforts following its acquisition by pepsico in 1987. in 2000, he was appointed executive chairman of pepsico and served in that position until 2003. in 2003, pitroda was appointed vice chairman and chief operating officer (coo) at verizon communications. in this role, he led verizon's overall operations and played a key
a behavior change method, or behavior change intervention, is a type of intervention used to change behaviors. behavior change methods can be categorized by the type of behavior that they are designed to change: - environmental: manipulate the environment in order to change behavior - social: change the social environment in order to change behavior - psychological: alter thoughts or emotions in order to change behavior behavior change methods can be further divided into those that use one or more of the following four approaches: - reinforcement: provide a reward after a desired behavior is displayed in order to strengthen
canal uno (formerly sitv) was a ecuadorian television station, founded on october 1, 1984. it was the first private television station in ecuador and, until its closure in 2013, the country's only commercial television broadcaster. canal uno was originally a joint venture between the ecuadorian government and the spanish media conglomerate telefónica. the latter acquired a controlling stake in the station in 1998, after which it became a wholly owned subsidiary of the company. in 2006, telefónica sold its majority stake in canal uno to the mexican media conglomerate televisa. in 2013, televisa announced that it would be closing down
bademiya is an iconic food stall and cafe located in the heart of manhattan's greenwich village. it has been in operation since 1985 and is run by bademiya family. the bademiya food stall has been a fixture in the heart of greenwich village since 1985, when it was opened by the bademiya family. the family has dedicated their life to running the business and serve up an iconic menu that features turkish-style mezes and fresh juices. the menu includes traditional favorites such as falafel, kofte, and shawarma, as well as unique items such as the baba ghanoush sandwich and the
brandon potter (born 6 august 1984) is an australian liberal national party politician who has been the member for morwell in the victorian legislative assembly since november 2014. potter was born in melbourne, and attended maribyrnong college and monash university, where he graduated with a bachelor of laws. he worked as an articled clerk before entering politics. he first contested a state election in 2010 as the liberal candidate for the seat of morwell. he was defeated by the incumbent labor mp, lynne kosky, but won the seat at the 2014 state election, defeating kosky by more than 7,000 votes.
marc raibert (born december 22, 1949) is an american engineer and entrepreneur. he is the co-founder and chairman of osterhout design group, a global design firm. he holds over 200 patents and has designed products for apple, blackberry, citroen, ford, infiniti, nike, toyota, and volvo. raibert was born in new york city. he received a bachelor's degree in mechanical engineering from the stevens institute of technology in 1971. after working as a engineer at general motors, raibert co-founded osterhout design group in 1984 with his then-wife karen osterhout. the company has since become one of the world's leading design firms,
