suleiman abdullah salim is a citizen of sudan who was sentenced to death in 2009 for crimes against humanity. suleiman abdullah salim was born in 1982 in the town of beit el-banat, located in the northern darfur region of sudan. he is a citizen of sudan, and was sentenced to death in 2009 for crimes against humanity. salim is accused of participating in the rape and murder of at least 44 civilians, including 21 children, in the town of el-fasher on february 25, 2008. salim has consistently denied any involvement in these crimes, and has claimed that he was kidnapped
joanne rachael lees (born 25 september 1973) is an english musician, singer and songwriter. she is the lead vocalist, guitarist and pianist of the alternative rock group joanne. lees was born in rochdale, lancashire, england. she attended rochdale girls' high school, where she was a member of the music staff. after leaving school, she worked as a trainee accountant before starting her music career in 1995. lees first came to prominence as the lead singer and guitarist of the alternative rock band joanne. the band released two albums, "joanne" (1996) and "chemtrails over england" (1998), before splitting up in 2000.
intergalactic medicine show (sometimes shortened to igms) is an american sketch comedy television series created by andy samberg and jorma taccone for hbo. the show is produced by 3 arts entertainment and stars samberg, taccone, and akiva schaffer. the series is set in the fictional universe of the intergalactic medicine show, a traveling troupe of performers who use their wit and humor to help people across the galaxies. the show revolves around the troupe's interactions with the various aliens they meet, as well as their own personal conflicts. the first season of igms was released on hbo on april 14,
the union cypress company operated a three-story sawmill in uniontown, ohio, from 1872 to 1968. the company was the first in the area to use a steam-powered sawmill. union cypress also produced lumber and pulp for export. the company was founded in 1872 by william d. dodd and his brother-in-law, charles l. webster. dodd had been working at a mill in west virginia when he met webster, who had just moved to the area. the two men decided to start their own mill and bought a plot of land on the banks of the scioto river near uniontown. they hired
a sawyer and began sawing lumber using a steam-powered sawmill. union cypress quickly became one of the largest mills in the region. the company expanded its operations by building a three-story sawmill in 1875 and a pulp mill in 1886. in 1899, the company purchased a plot of land near cleveland to build a paper mill. however, the great depression forced union cypress to sell its cleveland property in 1931. during world war ii, union cypress turned its attention to producing aircraft parts for the war effort. the company's mills were among the first in the country to use heavy
the voice uk is a british singing competition television series that began airing on itv on 29 january 2012. the show is produced by bbc studios and is based on the american show the voice. the voice uk is a singing competition television series that began airing on itv on 29 january 2012. the show is produced by bbc studios and is based on the american show the voice. the format of the show is similar to that of its american counterpart, with a panel of judges (formerly known as coaches) who help to select one or more contestants to
francis lillie pollock (february 4, 1876 – may 2, 1943) was an american artist who specialized in painting native american and western subjects. he was born in mount vernon, new york, the son of florence (née lillie) and charles pollock. he studied at the national academy of design, new york city (1898-1901), under thomas eakins and william merritt chase. in 1902, he traveled to mexico with his father and encountered the nahua people for the first time. influenced by their art, he adopted a style that combined realism with symbolism. pollock died in 1943 in santa fe, new mexico. francis
