asa fowler (february 23, 1811 – april 9, 1877) was an american politician and statesman. he served as the 4th governor of iowa from 1854 to 1857, and as the 9th united states secretary of war from 1861 to 1865. fowler was born in fowler, new york, on february 23, 1811. he moved to iowa in 1832 and became a farmer. in 1846, he was elected to the iowa house of representatives, where he served until 1854 when he was elected governor of iowa. fowler served as governor from 1854 to 1857. during his time as governor, fowler successfully advocated
the blackburn 2f.1 nautilus was a british racing car designed by gordon murray and made by mclaren racing limited, as a replacement for the mclaren m23. it was the first racing car to be designed and built in the uk since the end of world war ii, and was also the company's first carbon fibre car. the car entered six races in 2000, finishing fourth in the british formula 3 championship. the following year, it won the formula 3000 championship. the car was retired at the end of 2002. the nautilus was designed to compete in the 2000 british formula
george wood "squire" ebbert (june 10, 1810 – september 7, 1877) was an american farmer, banker and politician who served as the governor of indiana from 1865 to 1869. ebbert was born in licking county, ohio, to george and nancy (wood) ebbert. he grew up on a farm in delaware county, indiana, and attended the common schools. in 1832, ebbert moved to indiana and settled on a farm in what is now washington township, porter county. ebbert became a farmer and banker and was also involved in politics. he served as the county treasurer from 1842 to 1845 and as
in the united states, pay-to-stay is the term used for imprisonment where inmates must pay a fee to remain incarcerated. this fee is typically set at a higher amount than the cost of incarceration, which allows for the profit motive to influence prison policy and increase the number of inmates in jail. in some jurisdictions, the fee may be waived for low-risk inmates or those who cannot afford to pay. in others, it may be mandatory for all inmates. the fee can also be used to cover the costs of running the prison, such as salaries for guards and administrators.
jared schutz polis (; born may 12, 1971) is an american politician and businessman who has been the senior united states representative from colorado since 2013. a member of the democratic party, he previously served as the state's 32nd governor from 2009 to 2013. polis was born in boulder, colorado, the son of lois (née schutz) and jared schutz, a geophysicist and oceanographer. he was raised in a jewish family. polis has two younger sisters. he attended george washington university in washington, d.c., graduating with a degree in political science in 1993. after college, he worked as a field organizer
for then-united states representative rick larsen's successful campaign for u.s. senate from alaska in 1994. in 1996, he moved to denver to become a staff member for then-state senator john hickenlooper, who was running for governor of colorado. in 1998, polis was elected to the boulder city council. he served two terms before being elected mayor of boulder in may 2005, defeating incumbent mayor michael bowers in a close race. he was re-elected in 2009 with 71% of the vote and served two terms as mayor before being elected governor of colorado on november 3, 2009, defeating republican mark shultz
marvin hughitt (august 9, 1837 –– january 10, 1912) was an american farmer, businessman and politician who served as a u.s. representative from new york. born in wales, hughitt immigrated to the united states in 1847 with his parents. he attended the common schools and then worked on a farm in new york before becoming a merchant. in 1871, he married julia a. adair and they had five children. hughitt was a member of the new york state assembly (cattaraugus co.) in 1880 and 1881. he was elected as a republican to the forty-fourth congress and served from march 4,
baba bilal ogly aydamirov, also known as mashadibaba aydamirov, (born september 1, 1971, in tabriz, iran) is an iranian artist who uses traditional and contemporary techniques to create installations and paintings. aydamirov was born in tabriz, iran. he studied painting at the university of tehran, where he worked with professors such as mohammad-javad mizanin and abbas kiarostami. he then moved to france to study at the école nationale supérieure des beaux-arts in paris. there, he became friends with contemporaries like anselm kiefer and jr. aydamirov returned to iran in 1997 and has since exhibited his work throughout the country. his
menz gera midir is one of the most renowned icelandic poets of the 20th century. he was born in 1928 in reykjavik and died in 2002. menz gera midir's poetry reflects the tumultuous and complex history of iceland during the second world war and the post-war years. he was also a playwright, translator, and essayist. menz gera midir is one of the most renowned icelandic poets of the 20th century. he was born in 1928 in reykjavik and died in 2002. menz gera midir's poetry reflects the tumultuous and complex history of iceland during the second world war and the
ufuk şanlı is a turkish journalist and author who has written about kurdish affairs. ufuk şanlı was born in 1974 in the city of diyarbakır, turkey. he graduated from the department of journalism at istanbul university in 1999. he has worked as a journalist since then, first for the newspapers "hürriyet" and "yeni şafak", and later for the magazines "kurdistan report" and "zaman". he has also written books on kurdish issues, including "the kurds: nationalism and conflict" (2003), "the kurds: between mountain and sea" (2007), and "kurdistan: a history" (2009). şanlı is a member of the democratic society party (dtp),
letruska (foaled may 9, 2016) is an irish-bred, american-trained thoroughbred racehorse. as a two-year-old she won three of her four starts, including the grade i san felipe stakes and the grade ii lady's secret stakes. in the following year she was voted american champion two-year-old filly. letruska is a bay mare with a white blaze and three white socks bred in ireland by the breeding partnership of john magnier and jp mcmanus. she was sent to train in the united states with jockey mike smith. as a two-year-old letruska won three of her four starts, including the grade i san
stephan k. miller (may 6, 1968 – january 17, 2017) was an american computer scientist and professor of computer science at the university of california, berkeley. he is known for work on automatic parallelization, software engineering, and distributed computing. stephan miller was born on may 6, 1968, in cleveland, ohio. he received his b.s. in mathematics from ursinus college in 1989 and his m.s. and ph.d. degrees in computer science from the university of california, berkeley, in 1992 and 1995, respectively. after post-doctoral work at ibm research in 1995-1996, he became an assistant professor at the university of california, berkeley
in 1997. he was promoted to associate professor in 2001 and full professor in 2004. he served as the chair of the department of computer science from 2007 to 2014. miller's research focuses on automatic parallelization, software engineering, and distributed computing. his notable contributions include the development of a parallel programming model called simd (single instruction multiple data), which makes it possible to run multiple programs on a single processor using simd instructions; the development of a distributed system model called multi-root that provides transparent failover for multiple systems sharing a common root directory; and the development of a novel
something dangerous is the fifth solo album by australian singer-songwriter john butler. it was released on 10 october 2017 through island records. after four acclaimed albums as the frontman of the john butler trio, butler embarked on a solo career with something dangerous. the album was produced by butch vig (nirvana, garbage, fleetwood mac), and butler himself played all the instruments. "i wanted to make an album where i felt like i could just be myself," he said. "i didn't want to put anything up on screen or in my head that i couldn't let loose on the record." the
saint naum (bulgarian and macedonian: свети наум, sveti naum) (c. 356/357 – c. 424) was a bulgarian saint, bishop and martyr. the most reliable sources say he was born in the town of stara zagora in 356 or 357 ad and died in 424 ad. naum is venerated as a saint in the eastern orthodox, oriental orthodox, roman catholic and eastern catholic churches. he is also venerated as a martyr by the bulgarian orthodox church and the serbian orthodox church. naum is an icon of healing and patron saint of serbia and bulgaria. naum was born into a christian family
aaron nicholas cupples is an australian born, american-based composer, conductor and music educator. cupples was born in melbourne, victoria, australia, on october 22, 1963. he began his musical education at the age of six, studying the violin with his mother. at the age of 12 he began formal studies with john wallace at the university of melbourne, where he graduated with a bachelor of music in 1985. in 1988 cupples moved to the united states to study with bernard rands at the university of north texas college of music. there he completed his master of music degree in 1990. throughout
his career cupples has held positions as assistant professor of music at baylor university (1990-1997), assistant professor of music theory and composition at the university of utah (1998-2001), and associate professor of music theory and composition at chapman university (2002-present). he has also served as composer-in-residence at various institutions, including the university of california - santa barbara (2003), the university of utah (2004), and messiah college (2005). cupples currently serves as the director of chorus and orchestra studies for chapman university. cupples' compositions have been performed by ensembles throughout north america, europe and asia. highlights include premieres of works by
rebellion is a 2011 french historical drama film directed by luc besson and written by besson, michael haneke and stéphane brizé. it is based on the novel of the same name by alexandre dumas. the film stars matthias schoenaerts, jean-marc barr and charlotte gainsbourg. the film tells the story of a group of french aristocrats who join the french revolution in 1791, and their subsequent struggles against the french government. it was shot in belgium and france, and premiered in france on 7 october 2011. the film was a commercial failure, grossing only $8 million against its $50 million budget.
masha novoselova (maria novoselova, маша новоселова; born january 15, 1984) is a russian pianist and composer. novoselova was born in moscow, russia. she began playing the piano at the age of six and studied at the moscow state conservatory with evgeny kissin, graduating in 2004. novoselova has won several awards, including first prize at the prague spring international piano competition in 2004, first prize at the leeds international piano competition in 2005, and first prize at the seoul international competition in 2006. she is a laureate of several prestigious competitions, including the franz liszt international piano competition in budapest (2007),
the queen elisabeth competition in brussels (2008), and the tchaikovsky competition in moscow (2009). novoselova has been appointed a fellow of the royal college of music in london (2009) and a member of the royal academy of music in london (2011). she has also been awarded a number of prestigious scholarships, including a japan foundation fellowship (2008), a koussevitzky foundation grant (2010), and an avery fisher career grant from the new york philharmonic society (2011). novoselova's compositions include two symphonies, two concertos, five sonatas, three trios, four solo piano works, and numerous chamber pieces. her music has been performed by
the perth mint is australia's official bullion mint and produces a wide range of precious metals products, including gold, silver, platinum and palladium. the mint also produces commemorative coins and medallions. founded in 1829, the perth mint is one of the oldest mints in australia and was initially established to produce silver coins for the colony of western australia. in 1957, the mint began producing gold bullion coins, and since then it has expanded its product line to include platinum and palladium coins as well as commemorative medals and coins. in 2000, the mint became an official supplier of australian
john william benjamin warsap (18 may 1921 – 2 october 1987) was an english actor, best known for his roles in the bbc sitcoms the good life and only fools and horses. warsap was born in london, the son of rosa (née ward) and benjamin warsap, a clerk. he spent much of his early childhood in northampton before the family moved to harrow when he was seven. he left school at sixteen to work in a hat shop but soon quit to take a job as a railway porter. warsap made his stage debut in 1942 in the west end
production of boy friend. he appeared in variety shows and pantomimes before landing his first major role on television as wally cleaver's friend arnold tovey in the comedy series the good life (1958–61). he followed this with appearances as trigger happy taylor in only fools and horses (1981-1985), which made him an icon of british comedy. warsap also starred in several films, including the likely lads (1955), a taste of honey (1975), funeral arrangements (1981) and uncle boonmee who can recall his past lives (2010). warsap married actress joanna lumley in 1961; they had two children together before divorcing in
the wangchuan ji is a collection of buddhist scriptures originating from the tang dynasty. the wangchuan ji is unusual in that it is the only buddhist scripture that was not composed in sanskrit or chinese, but in a regional language, which is known today as wu. the wangchuan ji was compiled between 712 and 792 ad, and is one of the five classics of chinese buddhism. it consists of 108 volumes and covers a wide range of topics, including philosophy, meditation, and theology. it has been described as "the most important buddhist scripture after the lotus sutra." the wangchuan ji
schott music is one of the leading music retailers in the world and a subsidiary of schott ag. the company operates stores in over forty countries, selling a wide range of musical instruments, accessories and recordings. founded in 1695 by johann heinrich schott, schott music is one of the oldest music retailers in the world. the company has operations in over forty countries and sells a wide range of musical instruments, accessories and recordings. in addition to its retail stores, schott music operates music academies and schools, provides online sales and services, and distributes products through its network of independent
burton c. mossman (april 30, 1867 – september 3, 1936) was an american psychologist and educational reformer. mossman was born in amherst, massachusetts, on april 30, 1867. he received his undergraduate degree from amherst college in 1887 and his ph.d. from clark university in 1893. mossman began his academic career as an instructor at the massachusetts institute of technology (mit), where he worked until 1906. during that time, he also served as editor of the "mit campus magazine" and was a member of the phi beta kappa society. in 1906, mossman became the first professor of psychology at the university
of colorado, where he remained until 1922. during his time at colorado, mossman developed and taught one of the first courses in psychology undergraduate curriculum in the united states. in 1922, mossman moved to yale university, where he served as chairman of the department of psychology for six years. at yale, mossman established a program in experimental psychology which was among the first to be accredited by the american psychological association (apa). during his tenure at yale, mossman also served as president of the apa in 1928. in 1935, mossman retired from yale and moved to santa barbara, california. there
faizullah kakar (, , born 24 december 1947) is a pakistani politician who has been a member of the national assembly of pakistan, since august 2018. kakar was born on 24 december 1947 in the village of kakar in the swabi district of khyber pakhtunkhwa province. he completed his primary education in the village school before moving to lahore to attend government college lahore. kakar subsequently completed an external degree in political science from the university of sussex in the united kingdom. kakar started his career as a lecturer at government college lahore, where he served for two decades before
morris plan banks were part of a larger governmental effort known as the new deal. the morris plan banks were established in 1935 as part of the federal deposit insurance corporation (fdic) and were designed to help stabilize the banking system during the great depression. the morris plan banks were named after senator claude morris (d-n.j.), who helped create the fdic and was a key supporter of the plan. the morris plan banks were designed to provide short-term loans to banks that would be used to purchase government bonds. these loans would then be sold to the public, providing banks
