sarah (sally) jean rockey (born february 13, 1967) is an american actress and singer. she is best known for her roles as debra barone on the abc comedy-drama series "better off ted", and as dana scully on the fox science fiction drama series "the x-files". rockey was born in ann arbor, michigan, and raised in northampton, massachusetts. she attended northampton high school and then studied acting at the neighborhood playhouse in new york city. rockey's first television role was as a guest star on the nbc sitcom "the golden girls" in 1991. in 1993, she appeared in an episode of
