konjum salangai is a 1962 indian tamil-language film directed by k. balachander. the film stars sivaji ganesan, jayalalithaa, m. g. ramachandran and v. n. sundaram in lead roles. the story is set in a small town in the 1950s. goundamani (sivaji ganesan) is a wealthy man who has three daughters – kumari (jayalalithaa), menaka (m. g. ramachandran) and radha (v. n. sundaram). the girls are all different in terms of their personality and interests, but they are close to one another. kumari is tomboyish and likes to play cricket and fight with boys, menaka is studious and prefers reading books
the thracian sea (, thrakiko pelagos; ) is a salt water body located in the northeastern part of the mediterranean sea. it is named after thracia, one of the three historical regions that make up modern greece. the other two are macedonia and thrace. the thracian sea is bordered by bulgaria to the north, romania to the east and southeast, turkey to the south and west, and greece to the northwest. the sea has an area of 9,518 km2 (3,847 sq mi). its depth reaches a maximum of 230 m (755 ft) in the central area. the maximum width is
3,100 km (1,900 mi). there are numerous islands and islets in the sea: notably samothrace and mykonos. the international hydrographic organization defines the limits of the thracian sea as follows: on the north. a line joining cape matapan on the southwest coast of crete with cape sifnos on the northeast coast of lesbos. on the east. a line joining cape kaliakra on the southern coast of thessaly with cape arta on the northern coast of epirus. on the south. a line joining cape malea on the southwestern coast of crete with cape aspasia on the northeastern coast of lesbos. on
in biology, an organism is any living thing, from the smallest bacterium to the largest mammal. a complex organism typically contains many cells, which are able to carry out their own metabolic functions and interact with their environment. an organism can be a single cell or a large group of cells, and can range in size from a few micrometres to several hundred meters. in general, organisms are distinguished from plants and minerals by their lack of mobility (i.e. they are unable to move from one place to another), and by the presence of cells that can carry out metabolism.
aquil virani is a canadian artist, who is known for his oil paintings and drawings. he was born in 1963 in montreal, quebec, canada. aquil virani is a self-taught artist who began painting professionally in the early 1990s. he has exhibited his work widely, most notably at the centre georges pompidou in paris, the musée national d'art moderne in paris, and the museum of modern art in new york city. virani has been awarded several prizes, including the governor general's award for visual arts in 2004, and the prix italia in 2007. in 2012, he was awarded an honorary doctorate
