mahendranagar (nepali: महेन्द्रनगर) officially known as bhimdatta municipality, is a municipality in rupandehi district in the lumbini zone of southern nepal. the municipality was formed on 18 may 2014 by merging the existing bhimdatta and chhapra municipalities. bhimdatta is located at 26°6'47n 83°50'49e with an elevation of 2,480 metres (8,970 feet). it has an area of 1,611.93 square kilometres (626.73 sq mi). according to the 2011 nepal census it had a population of 64,565 people living in 16,572 individual households. the municipality is divided into 18 wards and the headquarter is located in ward no.1. the other wards are: ward
the oak ridge seminary (oak ridge female institute, o.r.f.i.) is a christian seminary in oak ridge, tennessee, united states. it has an enrollment of about seventy students. the seminary was founded in 1897 as the oak ridge female institute by the american baptist missionary convention and opened its doors to students in 1898. the name was changed to oak ridge seminary in 1951. the seminary offers undergraduate and graduate degrees in christian ministry and theology, with concentrations in bible and theology, church leadership, and missions. its faculty includes nationally recognized experts in their respective fields. the seminary is accredited by
the fatf blacklist (officially known as the sanctions list) is a list of individuals and entities that have been banned by the financial action task force (fatf), an international financial organisation. the blacklist was created in 1989 and has since been expanded to include more than 100 countries and jurisdictions. the fatf blacklist is the world's largest database of financial sanctions. it contains the names of individuals and entities that have been banned by the fatf because they are believed to be involved in money laundering, terrorist financing, or other financial crimes. the blacklist is updated every month, and it
is available to the public on the fatf website. the purpose of the blacklist is to deter financial crime by freezing the assets of banned individuals and entities. freezing assets can make it difficult for these people and organisations to access money or to conduct financial transactions. it also makes it more difficult for them to fund their activities. the blacklist has been very effective in deterring financial crime. as of september 2017, there were 138 individuals and 57 entities on the blacklist. this represents a total of $1.7 billion in frozen assets. the blacklist is administered by the financial
