tring rural is a civil parish in the borough of chatham in kent, england. the population of the parish at the 2011 census was 2,473. the parish is situated about south-east of maidstone, and occupies the south-west corner of the borough. it is bounded to the north by the thames estuary, to the east by the a282 road, to the south by the m25 motorway and to the west by maidstone borough boundary. the parish includes the villages of east peckham and west peckham, and part of the hamlet of tring green. the other hamlets in the parish are lower
