cutthroat peak is an 8,050-foot-elevation (2,450-meter) granitic peak in the sawtooth range of the western united states. the peak is located in salmon-challis national forest, east of the town of challis, idaho. cutthroat peak is an excellent destination for hikers and climbers because of its varied topography. the peak is composed of two peaks, east cutthroat peak (7,487 feet or 2,243 meters) and west cutthroat peak (7,527 feet or 2,248 meters), connected by a narrow ridge. the summit of east cutthroat peak is the higher of the two peaks and offers views of the sawtooth range, stanley peak, mount borah,
beat h. gähwiler (born february 10, 1940, in winterthur) is a swiss artist. he is known for his paintings, sculptures, installations, and photo works. beat h. gähwiler was born in 1940 in winterthur, switzerland. after completing an apprenticeship as a cabinetmaker, he studied art at the zurich school of applied arts from 1959 to 1962. in 1963 he moved to new york city, where he continued his studies at the school of visual arts and the pratt institute of art and design. in 1967 he returned to switzerland and settled in zürich. gähwiler’s paintings and sculptures explore the relationships between
form, light, and space. his installations often incorporate everyday objects into his compositions, creating unexpected interactions between familiar objects. his photo works explore the ways that photographic images can be used to create new meanings and perceptions. gähwiler has exhibited his work both in switzerland and abroad, including at the museum of modern art in new york city (1965), the solomon r. guggenheim museum in new york city (1972), the museum of contemporary art in chicago (1974), the hirshhorn museum and sculpture garden in washington d.c. (1977), and the centre georges pompidou in paris (1981). he has also been awarded
hans henrik ágost gábor, baron thyssen-bornemisza de kászon et thyssen-bornemisza de kármán (; 16 february 1907 – 6 december 1992) was a hungarian-born german industrialist, art collector, patron and politician. he was the founder and chairman of the thyssen group, a globally influential conglomerate. born in budapest, thyssen-bornemisza was the son of baron hans heinrich thyssen von aventoft and his wife countess amalie zichy de toba. after attending grammar school in hungary he studied law at the university of budapest and then at heidelberg university, where he received his doctorate in 1932. thyssen-bornemisza worked as a lawyer before starting his
own business ventures in the 1930s. he was one of the first businessmen to invest in heavy industry during the nazi period. in 1945, he fled to england after the war and returned to germany in 1949. he founded the thyssen group in 1952 and became its chairman in 1957. under his leadership, the company grew into one of the world's largest industrial conglomerates. thyssen-bornemisza was a member of the christian democratic union (cdu) from its foundation in 1949 until his retirement in 1982. he served as its treasurer from 1957 to 1962 and as its chairman from 1962 to
