archie clement (january 1, 1846 – december 17, 1924) was an american politician and businessman. he served as the 36th governor of ohio from 1899 to 1903. archie clement was born in 1846 in athens county, ohio, to farmer and millwright ebenezer clement and wife polly (née whitaker). he attended the common schools and graduated from athens high school in 1863. clement then studied law and was admitted to the bar in 1865. he began his political career as a member of the ohio house of representatives from 1883 to 1887. clement served as the 36th governor of ohio from
nancy marie brown (born 1959) is an american historian and author. she is the clarence d. little professor of history at stanford university, and a fellow of the american academy of arts and sciences. brown's work focuses on american history from the colonial period to the present, with a particular emphasis on race, gender, and class. her first book, "beloved community: race and politics in the new south" (1998), won the pulitzer prize. her other books include "the fortune of war: the unforgettable story of america's greatest economic disaster" (2000), "rising star: the life and times of anita hill" (2010),
wellington is a town in the nilgiris district of tamil nadu, india. it is located on the banks of the thirumalai river, about halfway between ooty and coonoor. the town is known for its hill stations and tea plantations. wellington was founded in 1818 by john wilson, an anglo-indian officer in the madras army, with the name "welkin valley". wilson had married an indian woman and decided to live in the nilgiris hills, which were then a part of the madras presidency. the town quickly grew and by 1835 had a population of 1,000. wellington became a municipality in 1877.
"invasion" is the fifth episode of the sixth season of the american medical drama grey's anatomy, and the 123rd episode overall. it was written by krista vernoff and directed by anthony edwards. it aired on abc in the united states on november 20, 2010. the episode follows the aftermath of a hurricane that hits seattle, causing numerous casualties. the hospital is overwhelmed with patients and staff members are struggling to provide care. the staff is further strained when they learn that one of their own, dr. derek shepherd (patrick dempsey), may have contracted the virus. the episode explores how the
