tailgate clothing company, corp. is a private company located in austin, texas. the company specializes in designing, manufacturing, and selling licensed collegiate and nfl apparel. tailgate clothing company was founded in 1995 by gary ray and brenton jobe. the company is a privately held corporation with its headquarters located in austin, texas. the company specializes in designing, manufacturing, and selling licensed collegiate and nfl apparel. the company's products are sold through specialty retailers and online retailers across the united states. in addition to selling apparel, the company also manufactures and distributes a wide range of collegiate and nfl fan gear
including hats, t-shirts, sweatshirts, and other accessories. tailgate clothing company has collaborated with a number of universities across the united states to create exclusive apparel lines that are sold only to students at the schools. the company has also collaborated with a number of nfl teams to create apparel lines that are sold only to fans at the team's stadium. the company has received numerous accolades over the years for its innovative designs and high quality products. in 2007, the company was awarded the prestigious sports business journal's prestigious "sports business award" for its contributions to the sports apparel industry.
mauger of hauteville (also latin malgerius or malegerius) (died 1093) was a norman nobleman and military leader who played a significant role in the history of normandy. he was the son of roger de malgeri, a nobleman from calabria. mauger is first mentioned in 1066, when he served as one of the commanders of the norman army that invaded england under duke william ii. he distinguished himself during the battle of hastings and was rewarded with numerous estates in england. in 1070, mauger married agnes, the daughter of robert, count of flanders. together they had two sons: roger and robert.
