texla is a ghost town in northern starr county, texas, united states. the town was founded in 1881 as a stop on the santa fe railroad. it was abandoned in 1903. texla is located on the east bank of the brazos river about north of fort worth. the town was settled in 1881 by a group of settlers from fort worth who named it for the ancient kingdom of tíxalá in present-day mexico. the town was originally built on a site that was selected because of its access to fresh water and fertile soil. texla prospered as a railroad stop
