westbourne is an affluent residential and shopping area located in the borough of bournemouth, in the english county of dorset. the area is bounded by the river poole to the east, northbourne avenue to the south, parkstone to the west and christchurch to the north. westbourne's retail centre includes high street stores such as debenhams, house of fraser, marks & spencer and john lewis, as well as luxury brands such as louis vuitton, lululemon athletica and yves saint laurent. the westbourne centre is home to a number of restaurants and bars, including wetherspoons, frankie & benny's and zizzi. westbourne is
(lucius?) plotius pegasus was a roman senator, astronomer, and astrologer who lived in the first century ad. he is most famous for his work on astrology and horoscopes, which he published in a series of books. plotius pegasus was born around the year ad 50 in rome. he studied astronomy and astrology under the famous astrologer publius cornelius scipio nasica. after publishing his first book on astrology in ad 78, plotius pegasus continued to produce books on the subject until his death in ad 99. plotius pegasus is best known for his work on horoscopes, which he published in a
robert dale rowell (april 8, 1955 – november 12, 2018) was an american author, journalist, and political commentator. he was the co-author, with bill o'reilly, of the new york times bestseller killing jesus. rowell was born in norfolk, virginia. he attended the university of virginia where he studied history and literature. rowell later worked as a reporter for the "norfolk virginian-pilot" before becoming a political analyst for fox news. rowell's first book, killing jesus, was released in october 2004 and became a new york times bestseller. the book is a biography of jesus christ based on historical evidence and critical
"mirai no museum" (translation: "future museum") is a japanese multimedia art project by artist yoko shimomura, which consists of a website and an accompanying app. the website, which is in japanese, features a collection of short films and animations about the future, created by shimomura and others. the app features the same content and allows users to interact with the films and animations. the project was first announced in february 2016, when shimomura revealed a series of conceptual drawings for the project at the tokyo designers week. the first film, "mirai no museum: from tomorrow", was released on the website
biltmore industries, inc., also known as biltmore forest industries and biltmore forest mills, is a family-owned business and the largest private-sector forest products company in north carolina. the company was founded in 1933 by brothers george and john biltmore, who first began producing lumber and paper products. today, the company produces a wide range of forest products, including plywood, oriented strand board (osb), hardwood flooring, lumber, paper products, and home furnishings. biltmore industries is headquartered in asheboro, north carolina and has operations in north carolina, south carolina, tennessee, georgia, and florida. the company employs more than 1,000 people across its
the least developed countries (ldcs) are a group of countries located in the world's poorest regions, characterized by low levels of development, especially in terms of human capital, economic freedom and institutional quality. ldcs were initially identified in the late 1960s and early 1970s as developing countries who had not achieved the level of development seen in more developed countries. the term is now often used more broadly to include all countries who are not members of the organisation for economic co-operation and development (oecd). there are currently 117 ldcs, which are concentrated in africa, the caribbean, and central asia.
the poorest ldcs tend to have the lowest levels of human development, including low levels of education, health and income. the causes of poverty and inequality within ldcs vary, but often include lack of access to resources (finance, land, natural resources), weak physical infrastructure, high levels of corruption and political instability. ldcs have beenidentified as a key focus for international aid organizations because they have a high rate of poverty and inequality relative to their economies. despite these challenges, ldcs have made progress in recent years. in 2014, for the first time since 1997, all ldcs recorded positive growth rates.
walter cowley (c.1500 – 1548) was an english poet and translator. cowley was born in london and educated at eton college. he became a gentleman pensioner of king's college, cambridge in 1525 and in 1529 he was elected to the fellowship of his college. he left cambridge without taking a degree in 1536, but he continued to live there as a pensioner until his death. cowley first gained notice as a translator, producing an edition of the works of ovid in 1538. he is best known for his poetry, most notably the poem "the masque of the red death" (1546),
barack hussein obama ii ( born august 4, 1961) is an american politician who served as the 44th president of the united states from 2009 to 2017. a member of the democratic party, he previously served as a u.s. senator from illinois from 2005 to 2009 and was the 44th governor of illinois from 2003 to 2005. he was first elected to the u.s. senate in 2004 and was re-elected in 2008, 2012, and 2016. obama was born in honolulu, hawaii, two years before the territory became a state. he spent most of his early childhood years in indonesia while
his father was stationed in the military there. after returning to the united states, he completed his undergraduate studies at columbia university and then worked as a community organizer in chicago before earning his law degree from harvard law school in 1991. he became a civil rights lawyer and professor, and ran for the u.s. senate in 2004. obama was elected senator in 2004, becoming the first african american to be elected to the u.s. senate from illinois, and received national attention for his campaign themes of change and social justice. in 2008, he was nominated for president by the
honeybunch is an indie pop band from los angeles, california. the band consists of vocalist and guitarist josie haddad, drummer jonathan pierce, and bassist alex gross. honeybunch was founded in early 2010 by josie haddad (vocals and guitar), jonathan pierce (drums), and alex gross (bass). the band released its first ep, "the first ep", in late 2010 on their own label, honeybunch records. the ep was well-received by music critics, receiving a 4/5 rating from indie website absolutepunk, as well as praise from publications such as the fader and popmatters. in early 2011, the band toured with popular indiepop band
grouplove. the band's second ep, "the second ep", was released in late 2011. it received a much more positive response than the band's debut ep, with absolutepunk awarding it a 9/10. the album was also well-received by music critics, with metacritic giving it a 73/100. in early 2012, honeybunch toured with popular alternative rock band death cab for cutie. in early 2012, honeybunch announced that they had signed to fueled by ramen records. the band's debut full-length album, "honeybunch", was released on february 3rd of that year. the album received mixed reviews from music critics, with some praising the band's
karlsøy church is a historic parish church in karlsøy municipality in møre og romsdal county, norway. the church is located on the island of karlsøya in the central part of karlsøy. it is part of the karlsøy parish in the sunnfjord deanery in the diocese of møre og romsdal. the first church on the island was probably built around the year 1000. it was a small wooden building that was replaced in the early 1600s with a larger stone church. the present church was built in a neo-gothic style in 1868-70 by the architect ole andreas paulsen. the church seats
fatima memorial system, founded in 1977, is a non-profit, international organization that promotes the values of peace, justice, and love. the fatima memorial system was founded in 1977 as a means of promoting peace, justice, and love. the organization has since grown to be one of the most respected and influential organizations working in the fields of peace and justice. the fatima memorial system's work is based on the belief that through education and awareness, people can work together to create a better world. the organization operates an education center in portugal, which provides lectures and workshops on a variety
forward-morges hc is an ice hockey organization based in morges, switzerland. the club was founded in 1954 and currently plays in the national league a, the top division of swiss ice hockey. forward-morges hc has played at the top level of swiss ice hockey since the early 1960s. forward-morges hc has a long and successful history in swiss ice hockey. the club was founded in 1954 and has since competed in the national league a, the top division of swiss ice hockey. the club has won two national titles (1968, 1997) and has made eight appearances in the championship final,
cryin' heart blues is a seventeen-track 2005 album by american blues rock band the allman brothers band. it was the group's first album in over a decade and marked the return of founding member duane allman. the album was recorded in 2002 and 2003, but due to various complications, it was not released until 2005. the album received mixed reviews from music critics, but it was a commercial success, peaking at number two on the billboard 200 chart. the allman brothers band reformed in 2002, but after recording three tracks for an album, they disbanded again due to creative differences.
iq classification is the practice by iq researchers of grouping people according to their intelligence quotients (iqs). the classification of intelligence is an important tool for investigating the etiology of iq, for identifying population subgroups with higher or lower iqs, and for predicting educational and occupational success. iq classification is used by psychologists, neuroscientists, geneticists, and other researchers who study intelligence. iq classification is also used by people who want to learn more about their own intelligence. there are many different ways to classify intelligence. the most common way to classify intelligence is to divide people into groups based on
their iqs. this is called the standardization approach. there are two main types of iq classification: psychometric and biological. the psychometric approach uses tests that have been developed over the years to measure intelligence. the biological approach uses information about the genes that people inherit from their parents. the two main types of iq classification are verbal and performance-based (or verbal-performance). verbal intelligence is measured by tests that ask people to think about words and solve problems involving words. performance-based intelligence is measured by tests that ask people to do things like solve puzzles or figure out how things work.
robert john odenkirk (born october 22, 1962) is an american actor, writer, and producer. he is known for his roles as saul goodman on the amc series breaking bad, tim whatley on the hbo series mr. show with bob and david, and jimmy mcgill on the fx series better things. odenkirk has also appeared in films such as the lookout, war of the worlds, and the nice guys. odenkirk was born in 1962 in saint louis, missouri, to margaret (née meyers), a teacher, and donald odenkirk, an engineer. he has two sisters and a brother. odenkirk attended washington university in
st. louis before transferring to the university of missouri-columbia, where he received his b.a. in theatre in 1984. he then moved to chicago and worked as an equity performer for three years before making his television debut on an episode of wings. odenkirk made his first appearance on breaking bad as saul goodman in 2008. he remained with the series until its conclusion in 2013, appearing in all but one season. odenkirk has since appeared in the director paul weitz's film the lookout and the anthology film crazy rich asians, both of which were released in summer 2018. in addition
falan is a town and municipality in the province of burgos, in the autonomous community of castile and león, spain. the municipality has a population of 4,849 (ine 2006). falan is located in the north-western part of the province of burgos, in the valley of the river fuentes de oñoro. the town is situated on the left bank of the river, at an altitude ranging between 380 and 430 m above sea level. the municipal area is bounded by the municipalities of valdezcaray and villanueva de la cañada to the north, san martín de la vega to the east, villanueva
de la cañada and valdezcaray to the south, and san martín de la vega and villanueva de la cañada to the west. the municipality includes part of the sierra de gredos mountain range. the soils are generally red and yellow clayey soils with a low percentage of organic matter. the municipality has a temperate climate with cold winters and hot summers. the town falan was founded by refugees from galicia in 1292. it was originally called "fuerte del santísimo sacramento" ("fortress of the holy sacrament"). in 1386 it was sacked by troops loyal to alfonso xi of castile; it was
richard edward connell jr. (october 17, 1893 – april 26, 1957) was an american author and dramatist. he is best known for his story "the most dangerous game" and the novel the great gatsby. connell was born in chicago, illinois, the son of irish american parents. he attended the university of notre dame and graduated with a b.a. in 1917. he then attended harvard law school, where he was a member of the delta kappa epsilon fraternity. after completing his law degree, connell served in the united states army during world war i. connell began his writing career in 1922
zhao wu (, 598 bce–541 bce), posthumously known as duke huan of qi, was a statesman and military general of the late spring and autumn period of ancient china. he was one of the most celebrated figures of his era, and is traditionally credited with leading qi to its greatest period of prosperity and power. zhao wu was born in 598 bce in the state of qi, during the spring and autumn period. after being orphaned at a young age, he became an apprentice to a butcher. he rose through the ranks of the qi military, eventually becoming a general.
in 527 bce, he led his forces to victory against neighboring states yang and zhen, establishing qi as an influential power in northern china. in 521 bce, zhao wu became the duke of qi. during his rule, qi became one of the most prosperous states in china. zhao wu died in 541 bce at the age of 68. he was posthumously honored with the title "duke huan of qi". zhao wu is widely considered one of the greatest statesmen and military generals of his era. he is credited with leading qi to its greatest period of prosperity and power. his
hu hanmin (; born in panyu, guangdong, china) is an artist who lives and works in beijing, china. she is best known for her paintings of cityscapes and people in traditional chinese clothing. hu hanmin was born in panyu, guangdong, china in 1984. after graduating from the beijing normal university with a bfa in fine arts in 2006, hu moved to beijing to study at the central academy of fine arts. in 2010, she debuted at the venice biennale with her installation "invisible cities". since then, she has participated in various group exhibitions including the 56th venice biennale (2015), the
maged el-kedwany aka maged nabil elkedwani (born january 30, 1949, in mansoura, egypt) is an egyptian sculptor who has worked in a variety of media including bronze, stone, marble, and plastic. his work is characterized by its abstract and fantastical elements, and often features creatures and figures with exaggerated features and anatomically-incorrect proportions. el-kedwany's sculptures are exhibited in a number of museums around the world, including the museum of modern art in new york city and the getty museum in los angeles. he has been awarded numerous prestigious awards, including the turner prize (1995), the praemium imperiale (2007), and the
the 1974 nba draft was the 28th annual draft of the national basketball association (nba). the draft was held on may 12, 1974 in new york city. the draft consisted of two rounds, with the first round taking place at the madison square garden in new york city and the second round taking place at the philadelphia spectrum in philadelphia. a total of 33 players were drafted in the two rounds, including four first-round picks. the draft was marred by allegations of bribery and corruption, which led to the convictions of several people, including then-nba commissioner walter kennedy and then-new
mo is a form of divination that is used in various parts of the world. it is most commonly associated with china, where it is known as 'chi'. mo is a form of divination that uses a number of methods, including casting lots, interpreting omens, and consulting a spirit medium. the aim of mo is to gain insight into the future, and to use this information to make decisions. there are many different types of mo, each with its own specific method and purpose. some examples include mo used in business, mo used to determine a person's fate, and mo
richard "dick" huemer (january 2, 1898 – december 3, 1973) was an american psychologist who made significant contributions to the field of cognitive science. huemer is best known for his work on the principle of level-of-processing and his theory of cognitive efficiency. huemer was born in detroit, michigan, on january 2, 1898. after completing his undergraduate studies at the university of michigan, he earned his doctorate from yale university in 1923. huemer then served as a professor at the university of illinois at urbana-champaign until his retirement in 1969. during his career, huemer published more than 100 papers and book
tim clissold (chinese name: 祈立天) is a chinese-born american artist who has been living and working in new york city since the early 1970s. clissold's work is characterized by its wit, humor, and irony, as well as its recurring motif of the human figure in a landscape or urban environment. in his paintings, sculptures, and mixed media installations, clissold investigates the ways in which humans relate to their surroundings, often employing humor and irony to explore the tensions between individual identity and social context. clissold was born in beijing in 1937 to a chinese father and an english mother. he
the allgaier group is a systems supplier for the automotive and motorcycle industry. the company has its headquarters in the city of augsburg, bavaria, germany. the allgaier group was founded in 1948 by hans allgaier. initially, the company produced parts for motorcycles. in the 1970s, allgaier began to produce complete motorcycles. in 1984, the company began to produce engines for motorcycles. today, the allgaier group produces engines, transmissions, and other components for motorcycles and cars. the company also produces exhaust systems and components for racing cars. the allgaier group is a major supplier of engines and components for motorcycles and
spalding house, also known as the cooke-spalding-latham house, is a historic home located at georgetown, delaware county, pennsylvania. it was built between 1815 and 1820, and is a 2 1/2-story, gable-fronted brick building with a hipped roof. it has a side wing and two rear additions. the house was restored in the early 1990s. the cooke-spalding-latham house was built by joseph cooke (1741-1812), a signer of the united states constitution; francis spalding (1754-1828), one of the founding fathers of the united states; and william latham (1781-1856), an american jurist, politician, and author. the house is now home to the georgetown
george aloysius carrell, s.j. (june 13, 1803—september 25, 1869) was an american jesuit priest and author who wrote extensively on theology and philosophy. carrell was born in hartford, connecticut, to a prominent irish-american family. he attended the college of the holy cross in worcester, massachusetts, where he studied theology. carrell was ordained a priest in 1827. he served as a missionary in new orleans, louisiana from 1835 to 1839. he then served as a professor of philosophy at the jesuit college of saint louis from 1839 to 1865. carrell's most famous work is his book "a history of philosophy", which
viscount fauconberg, of henknowle in the bishopric of norwich, was a british peer. fauconberg was the son of the hon. frederick fauconberg and his wife, the hon. isabella, daughter of the 2nd viscount gage. he succeeded to his father's titles in 1892. he served as captain of the norfolk yeomanry from 1892 to 1899 and as lord lieutenant of norfolk from 1899 to 1910. in 1902, he was appointed a deputy lieutenant for norfolk. fauconberg was also a member of the royal yacht squadron and the norfolk hunt club. he died in december 1938 at henknowle and was buried in
