james j. snidero (born may 29, 1958) is a former american football player and coach. he played professionally as a defensive back in the national football league (nfl) for the buffalo bills and dallas cowboys. he also served as the head coach of the nfl's cleveland browns and philadelphia eagles, and the defensive coordinator of the tampa bay buccaneers. snidero was born in buffalo, new york, and attended archbishop molloy high school in queens, new york. he played college football at the university of massachusetts amherst. after playing in the nfl for six seasons, he resigned as eagles defensive coordinator
