mount lyell is the highest point in the trinity alps of california, at 8,163 feet (2,569 m) above sea level. the peak is located in the trinity alps wilderness, part of the inyo national forest. the mountain was first named in 1853 by john c. fremont for geologist charles lyell. fremont mistakenly thought that the peak was part of the scottish mountaineering club's mountaineer peak, which is 8,128 feet (2,559 m) high. the true summit of mount lyell was not discovered until 1912 by a.e. nordhoff and a.j.m. smith. it was named for the geologist charles lyell, who formulated the
baba raul canizares (24 september 1955 – 3 december 2017) was a spanish football manager, who was most recently in charge of cd lugo. canizares began his coaching career as an assistant at cd lugo, before taking over as manager in 2003. he led the club to la liga's top division for the first time in 2006–07, but was sacked after a poor start to the 2007–08 season. he subsequently had spells in charge of atlético madrid and racing santander, but resigned from both clubs after failing to win promotion. canizares returned to cd lugo in november 2016, and led
the saint francis xavier cathedral parish , kabankalan city is a roman catholic parish in the philippines. it is under the jurisdiction of the archdiocese of lipa. the parish was established on july 9, 1952, by father agustin gonzales, s.j. in an old spanish mission chapel at the foot of mount kanlaon. the present cathedral was built from 1984 to 1986 under the leadership of fr. teodoro de guzman and fr. gerardo de castro with the financial support of the knights of columbus. it has a regular congregation of 3,000 and a total membership of 10,000, comprising mainly kabankalan natives
the saga system is a role-playing game engine originally designed by bioware for the video game jade empire. released in november 2005, it was later used in a number of other video games including mass effect 2, dragon age ii and knights of the old republic ii. in july 2009, bioware released an expansion pack for jade empire, entitled the saga continuum. the saga system is a game engine that was designed by bioware for the video game jade empire. released in november 2005, it was later used in a number of other video games including mass effect 2, dragon
age ii and knights of the old republic ii. the saga system is built on the unreal engine 3 game engine. the saga system features a modular design which allows developers to create their own content without having to modify the core engine code. this modularity also makes it easy to port saga games to new platforms, as well as to upgrade and improve them over time. the saga system allows players to control characters using a variety of input devices, including keyboard, mouse and game controllers. character movement is based on a physics engine which allows for realistic interactions
nns aradu (f89) (meaning "thunder" in telugu) is an indian ocean island nation located in the lakshadweep sea. the nation comprises nine islands and three islets, with a total land area of 2.5 square kilometres. nns aradu is the smallest and least populous nation in the lakshadweep islands. the nation's capital is at aradu island. the population of nns aradu was not reported by the government, but was estimated to be less than 1,000 people in 2011. nns aradu is a member of the united nations and the commonwealth of nations. it has limited diplomatic relations with countries in south
crista samaras is an american inventor, businesswoman and philanthropist. crista samaras was born in rochester, new york, to parents of greek descent. her father, george samaras, was a chemist and inventor. after graduating from high school in 1972, crista studied chemistry at the university of rochester. in 1978, she obtained her degree in chemical engineering from the university of texas at austin. after completing her undergraduate studies, samaras worked as a research scientist for 3m company in st. paul, minnesota. in 1985, she founded her own company, crista technologies inc., which developed environmentally-friendly products such as paint and sealants. in
2002, she sold crista technologies to the chemours company. since 2009, samaras has been the co-chairman of the board of trustees of mount saint mary's college in maryland. she has also served on the boards of directors of several charitable organizations, including the american red cross and the national multiple sclerosis society. in 2013, samaras was named one of forbes' "30 most powerful women" in business. in addition to her work as an inventor and businesswoman, samaras is a philanthropist. she has donated money to numerous charities, including the special olympics and the children's hospital of philadelphia. she also funds
george harry yardley iii (november 3, 1928 – march 11, 2015) was an american theoretical physicist who made significant contributions to the theory of the strong interaction and the development of quantum field theory. yardley was also a leading proponent of the quark model, which is a theoretical model of the strong interaction. yardley was born in 1928 in new york city, and obtained his b.a. from brown university in 1950. he then obtained his m.a. from yale university in 1952, and his ph.d. from princeton university in 1956. after completing his doctorate, he remained at princeton as a post-doctoral
fellow until 1958. in 1958, yardley moved to the university of chicago, where he became a faculty member in 1960. in 1974 he moved to the california institute of technology, where he remained until his retirement in 2000. during his career, yardley made significant contributions to the theory of the strong interaction and the development of quantum field theory. his work on the quark model played a significant role in developing this field. in addition, yardley was also a leading proponent of the philosophy of science, and published extensively on this topic. he died on march 11, 2015 at the
mufti wali hasan tonki (born; 1924 - died; 2009) was a pakistani religious scholar and mufti. he was born in 1924 in the tonki area of abbottabad district, british india (now in pakistan). he received his early education from his father, maulvi hasan, a religious scholar and teacher. he then studied at darul uloom deoband and later at the islamic university of madinah. he also studied at the al-azhar university in cairo, egypt. he served as a lecturer at the islamic university of madinah and as the dean of the faculty of sharia law at the same university. he also
kathy l. saltzman (born june 4, 1955) is an american politician who is the senior united states senator from new york. a member of the democratic party, saltzman has served in the senate since 2001. saltzman was born in brooklyn, new york, and attended public schools there. she earned her b.a. in political science from suny albany in 1977 and her j.d. from columbia law school in 1981. she worked as an assistant district attorney in kings county, new york from 1981 to 1984, and then became a criminal defense lawyer. saltzman was elected to the new york state assembly
in 1986, serving until 1994. she then served as counsel to governor mario cuomo from 1994 to 1996 and deputy mayor for operations under mayor rudolph giuliani from 1996 to 1998. from 1998 to 2001, she was the united states attorney for the southern district of new york. in 2001, saltzman was elected to the united states senate, defeating republican incumbent rick lazio by a wide margin. she became the first female jewish senator in american history and also the first democrat from upstate new york to serve in the senate since herbert h. lehman left office in 1962. saltzman
ramzi bin al-shibh (, ; also transliterated ramzi binalshibh, ramzi bin al-sheibh, and ramzi bin al-shibh al-ajmi) was an accused conspirator in the september 11 attacks. born in mecca, saudi arabia, in 1975, bin al-shibh moved to the united states in the early 1990s and became a naturalized u.s. citizen. he resided in virginia and was employed as a systems engineer for a defense contractor. bin al-shibh is alleged to have played a key role in the planning and execution of the september 11 attacks, which killed 2,996 people. he was captured by u.s. forces in may 2002 and was
subsequently indicted by federal prosecutors on charges of conspiracy, murder and other crimes related to the attacks. in november 2003, he pleaded not guilty to all charges and was held without bail pending trial. on march 7, 2005, bin al-shibh was found guilty on all counts and was sentenced to death. his sentence was later commuted to life imprisonment without parole in december 2006 by then-president george w. bush. in may 2006, bin al-shibh sued cbs corporation for defamation over an episode of its show "the practice" that aired in march 2005. the episode portrayed him as a terrorist mastermind.
jeet is a 1972 indian hindi-language action film directed by k. r. vijaya kumar and produced by the kasturi pictures banner. the film stars dharmendra, hema malini, sanjeev kumar and music composed by laxmikant-pyarelal. the story is set in the backdrop of the indo-pakistani war of 1971. jeet is a brave and patriotic indian soldier who is forced to flee his homeland after being falsely accused of cowardice. he ends up in pakistan, where he joins the pakistani army and becomes a successful soldier. one day, he is given a chance to redeem himself by rescuing a group of indian
catherine cornaro (25 november 1454 – 25 october 1530) was an italian renaissance composer and singer, as well as a highly influential teacher of music. she is considered one of the most prominent figures of the early baroque era. catherine cornaro was born in corneto, a small town in the province of udine, in northeastern italy. at the age of nine she moved with her family to venice, where she was soon discovered by the leading composers of the day, including giovanni pierluigi da palestrina and antonio lotti. she began her formal music training at an early age under the
guidance of giovanni gabrieli and later antonio maria lotti. in 1479 cornaro married the wealthy patrician francesco maria ii della rovere, who helped support her career. cornaro's first major compositions were for vocal and instrumental ensemble, including motets and madrigals. she also wrote chamber music, including a series of sonatas for two violins and continuo. her most famous works are her operas, mostly composed during the 1510s. her most famous opera is "marriage of figaro", which has been performed throughout europe and remains one of the best-known operas in history. catherine cornaro died in venice in 1530 at the age
