a filing cabinet (or sometimes file cabinet) is a tall chest of drawers, usually located in an office, containing folders for organizing papers. the earliest filing cabinets were built in the 18th century, and were usually made of wood. they were usually large, heavy desks with several drawers, and were used to store paperwork such as bills, ledgers, contracts, and letters. the first filing cabinets were designed to store paper alphabetically, by subject, or by date. they were also designed to be easily accessible so that the owner could find what they wanted quickly. today, filing cabinets are still commonly
the waag (waegh) is a former weigh house in haarlem, netherlands. it is now part of the museum boijmans van beuningen. the waag was originally built in 1424 as part of a defensive structure around the city of haarlem. the waag was used as a weighing station for goods entering and leaving the city. in 1614, the waag was converted into a public museum. today, the waag is one of the most popular museums in haarlem, with visitors coming from all over the netherlands and even from abroad. the museum contains a variety of art objects, including paintings by rembrandt
