arthur albert link (may 24, 1914 – march 21, 1986) was an american chemist who specialized in the study of organic and inorganic compounds. he was particularly interested in the structure and reactivity of carbon-containing molecules. born in st. louis, missouri, link earned his bachelor's degree from the university of missouri in 1936. he then earned his doctorate from the university of chicago in 1941. after a year of postdoctoral study at the university of california, berkeley, link was appointed an assistant professor at the university of missouri in 1942. he remained at missouri for the rest of his career,
retiring as a professor emeritus in 1978. link's work focused on organic chemistry, specifically on the structure and reactivity of carbon-containing molecules. he is particularly noted for his work on carbocations, which are carbon-containing radicals that can exist in two different configurations: as c=o double bonds or as c=n triple bonds. in addition to carbocations, link also studied radical reactions and molecular coordination complexes. link was elected to the national academy of sciences in 1969 and to the american academy of arts and sciences in 1970. he received the national medal of science in 1977 and was awarded the nobel
the characteristic of cynocephaly, or cynocephalus , is a head and face that are significantly larger than normal for the child's age and sex. the skull may be misshapen, with a domed or elongated shape, or the forehead may be unusually high. there is often an elongated nose or a wide mouth. the eyes may be large and protruding, or they may be close-set. the chin may be prominent. cynocephaly is a birth defect that affects the growth of the brain and skull. it is most common in boys, and it can cause major problems with development and health. cynocephaly
is caused by a problem with the way the brain grows in the womb. most cases of cynocephaly are caused by a problem with the way the brain grows in the womb. this problem is called craniosynostosis . in craniosynostosis , the bones that make up the skull don’t grow evenly. this can cause the skull to become domed or elongated, or the forehead to become unusually high. other causes of cynocephaly include genetic defects, injuries during birth, and infections during pregnancy. most cases of cynocephaly are caused by a problem with the way the brain grows in the womb,
zhìshēng was a chinese buddhist monk who lived in the tang dynasty. he is best known for his commentary on the mahāyāna mahāparinirvāṇa sūtra. zhisheng was born in 788 in zhishi county, shandong province. he was an ordained buddhist monk at the age of thirteen and studied under various masters before founding his own school of buddhism in 810. in 825, he travelled to india to study under the buddhist monk dharmakīrti and returned to china in 829 with a large body of knowledge on indian buddhism. in 832, he wrote his commentary on the mahāyāna mahāparinirvāṇa sūtra, which became
