biltmore village, formerly best, is a historic district in the u.s. state of north carolina. it is a planned community founded in the late 1920s as a replica of an english country estate, and is now a popular tourist destination. biltmore village is located in asheville, north carolina, about northeast of downtown. the district encompasses about of land and contains about 100 buildings, most of which are tudor revival or georgian revival architecture. the centerpiece of the village is biltmore estate, a national historic landmark and one of the largest private homes in the united states. the estate includes more
than 200 acres (81 ha) of gardens and forest, as well as twenty-six structures, including thirteen bedrooms and thirteen bathrooms. the community was founded in 1928 by george w. vanderbilt ii and his wife alva vanderbilt as a replica of an english country estate. the original name for the community was best, but it was renamed biltmore village in 1933 after george w. vanderbilt's father, george w. vanderbilt i, who had died two years earlier. the community was designed to be self-sufficient, with its own power plant and farm. today, biltmore village is a popular tourist destination; it receives about
