mukhtaran bibi (; born ), now known as mukhtar mai, is a pakistani human rights activist who has been working for the rights of women and girls since the early 1990s. mukhtar mai was born in the village of dargah mandi, in the district of chakwal, punjab, pakistan. she married when she was just 16 years old, and had two daughters. in 1990, she founded the association for the protection of rights of women and girls (aprwg), with the goal of raising awareness about the abuses suffered by women in pakistan. mai became a symbol of resistance against pakistan's conservative
