ștefan constantinescu, (born 10 february 1968), is a romanian politician who has been president of romania since 2004. he served as prime minister of romania from 2000 to 2004, and again from 2007 to 2008. constantinescu was born in bucharest, romania on 10 february 1968, into a middle-class family of intellectuals. after graduating from the university of bucharest with a degree in law, he worked as a lawyer before entering politics. in 2000, constantinescu was elected prime minister of romania, becoming the first member of the national liberal party (pnl) to hold the position. his government was marked by strong
