kandla, officially deendayal port, is a seaport and industrial city on the eastern coast of india in the state of gujarat. it is located on the gulf of cambay, about north of the state capital gandhinagar. the city has a population of over 1 million people. kandla is named after maharaja kandla singh, who founded the city in 1877. the port was commissioned by the british in 1887 and became a major base for trade with central asia, africa and the middle east. the city's economy is based on shipping, fishing, textiles, cement and other manufacturing. kandla port is also
was the 2nd mizuno daimyō of yamagata domain, and the 18th lord of the mizuno house. he served as the head of the mizuno clan for 45 years from 1892 to 1929. mizuno tadahiro was born on october 19, 1848 in what is now yamagata prefecture. he was the son of mizuno masatomo and a lady named satō, who was a relative of the satō clan daimyō of shimabara domain. mizuno tadahiro succeeded his father as daimyō of yamagata domain in 1892. mizuno tadahiro was one of the most important figures in early meiji period japan. as daimyō of yamagata
domain, he played a leading role in the development of the domain and helped shape its character. he also played an important role in the modernization process, spearheading efforts to modernize agriculture, industry, and education in the domain. mizuno tadahiro was a highly respected figure in early meiji period japan. he was considered to be a shrewd and effective leader, and his administrative skills were praised by many observers. he also had a reputation for being a fair and just daimyō, and he often acted as an intermediary between yamagata domain and the central government. mizuno tadahiro died on september
