la rochelle. in 1990, gaillac reached the final of the coupe de france for the second time, but lost to stade français. the club reached the final of the heineken cup in 2001, but lost to leicester tigers. in 2003, gaillac reached the final of the european challenge cup, but lost to biarritz olympique. the club reached the final of the heineken cup again in 2006, but lost to toulon. in 2007, gaillac reached the final of the european challenge cup again, this time beating biarritz olympique 28–24 on aggregate. union athlétique gaillac won its first top 14 title in
pj's coffee of new orleans is an independently owned, family-owned coffee company located in the historic french quarter of new orleans, louisiana. pj's coffee was founded in 1978 by phil and joanne jordan. the jordans were natives of new orleans and had always been passionate about coffee. they opened their first coffee shop on royal street in the heart of the french quarter. the shop quickly became a popular gathering place for locals and tourists alike and the jordans quickly realized that they had found their true passion in life - brewing beautiful, rich coffee for everyone to enjoy. today,
neuroprivacy, or "brain privacy," is a concept that encompasses the privacy of individuals' brains, thoughts, and memories. it has been defined as "the right of individuals to protect their mental privacy, including the right to avoid disclosure of their personal thoughts, memories, and experiences." the neuroprivacy debate has been ongoing since the early days of neuroscience. scientists have long been interested in understanding the workings of the brain, and have been concerned about the potential for unauthorized access to individual thoughts and memories. in response, many people have advocated for measures to protect brain privacy. one of the first efforts
to address brain privacy was made in the early 20th century. at that time, scientists were experimenting with hypnosis and psychoanalysis, techniques that could be used to access individual thoughts and memories. concerns about these practices led some individuals to advocate for strict measures to protect brain privacy. in 1961, the u.s. congress passed the national security act amendments of 1961 (public law 87-297), which created the central intelligence agency (cia). one of the provisions of this law was a ban on unauthorized access to intelligence records. this law was designed to protect intelligence records from being accessed by unauthorized
fort toronto, also known as fort portneuf, was a british military fort in what is now the city of toronto, ontario, canada. construction started in 1793 and was completed in 1813. the fort was originally situated on the south bank of the don river, opposite the mouth of the humber river. it was later relocated to its present location on the eastern shore of garrison creek. the fort served as a key defensive point during the war of 1812 against american forces. in 1853, it was renamed fort york in honour of the duke of york, who later became king
edward vii. the fort was decommissioned in 1870 and demolished in 1883. fort toronto was one of several forts built by the british to defend their north american colonies against american incursions during the war of 1812. construction started in 1793 and was completed in 1813 at a cost of £289,000 (approximately $6 million in 2006 dollars). the original fort was located on the south bank of the don river, opposite the mouth of the humber river. it was later relocated to its present location on the eastern shore of garrison creek. the fort served as a key defensive point
kristina meneši (; born 28 october 1977) is a croatian actress, model and singer. kristina meneši was born in zagreb, croatia, on 28 october 1977. she started her acting career in the croatian television series "neretva" in 2003. she has since starred in several other croatian television series, including "kraljević" (2005), "divlji dom" (2006), "priča o sherlocku holmesu" (2007) and "crni trg" (2008). in 2005, she also starred in the slovenian film "srečni ljudje". in 2006, meneši represented croatia in the eurovision song contest with the song "ljubav je…". she finished in eighteenth place with 114 points. in 2007, she
hilarie ros burton (born july 1, 1982) is an american actress and former fashion model. burton became known for her roles as margo timmins on the nickelodeon television series are you afraid of the dark? (2005–2010), penny parker on the abc sitcom modern family (2009–2015), and cathy mcmorris rodgers on the fox television series the office (2005–2013). burton also had recurring roles on the nbc sitcom 30 rock (2007–2013) and the cbs sitcom the big bang theory (2007–2013). she has also starred in films such as big miracle (2008), corpse bride (2005), and wonder boys (2000). burton was a judge
daviesia brevifolia, commonly known as leafless bitter-pea, is a perennial flowering plant in the family fabaceae. it is endemic to the south-west of western australia. daviesia brevifolia grows as a prostrate shrub 2–4 m tall with slender, branched stems and leaves that are reduced to simple, strap-like lobes 4–10 cm long and 1–2 cm wide. the flowers are arranged in terminal panicles up to 25 cm long, each flower with five sepals and five petals. the petals are white, pink or red, and the stamens are numerous and protrude beyond the petals. the fruit is a capsule 10–15 cm long
the sheraden homestead is located at 2803 sheraden road in richmond, virginia. it is a large, two-story, frame dwelling with a hip roof and clapboard siding. the interior features large rooms and high ceilings, original woodwork, and federal period mantels. the property was acquired by the richmond history museum in 1985. the sheraden homestead is a major historic site in richmond, virginia. it is located at 2803 sheraden road in the sheraden section of the city. the property was acquired by the richmond history museum in 1985, and has been listed on the national register of historic places since march
weobley castle was a ringwork and bailey castle built in the late 12th century by roger de montgomery and his wife, ada. the castle passed through a number of hands over the centuries, but was largely abandoned in the 15th century. it was damaged during the english civil war and fell into disrepair, but was restored in the early 20th century. it is now a tourist attraction. the original castle was built on a rocky outcrop overlooking the river wye about 1 kilometer (0.6 miles) south-east of hereford. it was circular, with a diameter of about 50 meters (160 feet).
randy mann is a retired american soccer player who played as a defender. randy mann was born on march 4, 1966 in fort lauderdale, florida. he attended deerfield beach high school, where he was a two-time all-state soccer player and captain of the varsity soccer team. mann played college soccer at the university of north carolina at chapel hill, where he was a first team all-american and acc defensive player of the year in 1987. mann was drafted by the kansas city wizards in the first round (10th overall) of the 1988 mls college draft. he made his professional debut
on april 25, 1988, playing 78 minutes in a 2-1 victory over the new england revolution. mann missed most of the 1989 season with an injury, but helped the wizards reach the playoffs that year. he played 76 minutes in the eastern conference championship game against tampa bay rowdies, but the wizards lost 3-2. mann played 73 minutes in a playoff loss to d.c. united in 1990. in march 1991, mann was traded to the dallas burn for mark abbott and mike magee. he played three seasons with dallas, helping them to win two mls cups (1996 and 1997). in
