"pink triangle" is a song by american rock band kiss. it was released in february 1979 as the lead single from the album dynasty. the song was written by gene simmons, paul stanley, and ace frehley. "pink triangle" is a hard rock song with elements of funk. it is heavily influenced by the band's earlier sound and features a riff similar to that of "god of thunder". the song is also notable for its prominent bassline, which was played by frehley. the song reached number six on the united states "billboard" hot 100 chart and number two on the "billboard"
hot rock songs chart. it also reached number one in australia and number four in canada. the song was certified gold by the riaa in march 1979. the song has been covered by various artists, including lita ford, alice cooper, and whitesnake. "pink triangle" was written by gene simmons, paul stanley, and ace frehley in december 1978 during the dynasty tour. the song was originally titled "in the pit". the song was first performed live on february 18, 1979 at the universal amphitheatre in los angeles as part of kiss' dynasty tour. "pink triangle" is a hard rock song with
twin dragons (also known as shuang long and shen long) are a pair of mythical creatures from chinese mythology and folklore. they are usually depicted as a pair of dragons, but can also be other creatures with two heads and two tails, such as a lion and a snake. they are often considered to be the sons of the dragon king, and they are said to be able to breathe fire. the twin dragons are often used in chinese art and culture to represent the dual nature of things, such as male and female, good and evil, etc. they are
dienia, commonly called snout orchids, is a genus of about 45 species of orchids in the family orchidaceae. most are found in the tropics, but a few species are found in temperate regions. one, d. angustifolia, is endemic to the united states east of the rocky mountains. the genus is characterised by a short and broad stalk with a long, narrow, pointed snout. the flowers are typically small and bright yellow or white, and are borne in clusters on a long stem. the name dienia is derived from the ancient greek word "dianthus", meaning spikelet. dienia is one of the
most diverse genera of orchids, with 45 species divided among eight subgenera. species in the subgenus "dipladenia" have thin, wiry stems and densely crowded flowers; those in "dianthium" have more robust stems and flowers that are less densely crowded. there is considerable variation within each subgenus, with some species having stems as much as long and flowers as large as a dinner plate. most dienias grow in moist soils near water sources, but a few—including d. angustifolia—are found in dry areas. most require full sun but a few—including d. occidentalis—can tolerate partial shade. some dienias can be propagated from cuttings,
gwen taylor (born 19 february 1939) is a welsh singer, songwriter and television personality who rose to prominence in the 1960s. born in pontypridd, gwen began her career performing with the group the four aces. the group achieved minor success in the uk and mainland europe, but it was their 1966 single "i know what i want" which propelled them to stardom. the song reached number one on the uk singles chart and became a fixture in british popular music. in 1967, gwen released her debut solo album, gwen taylor. the album yielded two hit singles, "i'm just a woman"
the 2020–21 dfb-pokal was the 78th season of the german football knockout cup competition. it began on 9 august 2020 and concluded on 12 may 2021 with the final at the olympiastadion in berlin. bayern munich were the defending champions. the draw for the first round took place on 26 may 2020, and saw eight clubs pitted against each other. the matches were played on 9, 16, 23, 30 and 6 august 2020. the draw for the second round took place on 10 july 2020 and saw the eight clubs who made it through the first round paired up again.
