econetic is a tradename for certain car models made by the german automaker volkswagen group. the term was first used in 1998 for a concept car designed by jörg müller. volkswagen group, or vw as it is commonly known, is a multinational automotive company headquartered in wolfsburg, germany. the company was founded in 1937 by the merger of several german automakers, including auto union and audi. today, vw employs more than 355,000 people worldwide and sells around 10 million vehicles per year. the volkswagen group's core brands are audi, bentley, bugatti, ducati, golf, lamborghini, land rover, man, maserati, porsche, seat
the critical psychiatry network (cpn) is a global organization of clinical and research psychiatrists who share a commitment to excellence in psychiatry. we foster dialogue and collaboration among clinicians and researchers to improve the quality of psychiatric care. the cpn was founded in 2001 as a forum for exchanging ideas and developing best practices in psychiatry. we work to improve access to mental health services, promote innovative treatments, and advance research that supports quality care for patients with mental illness. we are committed to building bridges between psychiatry and other medical disciplines, including neurology, physical medicine and rehabilitation, cardiology, and
vedaranyeswarar temple is a hindu temple dedicated to the god vedaranyeswarar, located in the city of thanjavur in the indian state of tamil nadu. the temple is one of the 12 jyotirlingas, and is one of the most renowned hindu temples in india. it is also one of the longest-existing temples in india, having been built during the reign of the pandyan dynasty (12th century to 15th century) the temple complex covers an area of over 130 acres (53 ha), and includes a number of other shrines, including a "naalukkaram" (water tank) and a "prakaram" (monument). the main shrine is
tony waldrop (born december 29, 1951) is an american jazz trumpeter. waldrop was born and raised in detroit, michigan. he started playing the trumpet in the sixth grade, and began his professional career in the early 1970s. waldrop first gained national attention as a member of the jazz fusion group weather report, which he joined in 1974. he left the group in 1978, but returned to it for a series of reunion tours in the 1990s. waldrop has also worked extensively as a solo artist, and has released several albums on his own label. he has been nominated for four
gaius blossius (; 2nd century bc) was a roman military general and statesman. he served as consul in 195 bc and as dictator in 193 bc. blossius was born in the town of lanuvium, about thirty miles northwest of rome, to a noble family. after studying philosophy in athens, he returned to rome and began his political career as a supporter of the populares faction. he served as quaestor in 191 bc and as praetor in 190 bc. in both positions, he showed himself to be an effective administrator. in 187 bc, he served as legate to the army fighting
the second macedonian war. he distinguished himself at the battle of cynoscephalae, where he routed a large macedonian force. for his victory, blossius was awarded the cognomen "pelopidas". in 186 bc, blossius was elected consul, an office he held with distinction. as consul, he campaigned successfully against the lusitanian rebels and secured roman possessions in iberia. in 185 bc, he was appointed dictator for a year to deal with the social war, a civil conflict between rome's working classes and the wealthier patricians. as dictator, blossius proved to be an effective leader; under his rule, the social war came to
tangata is a genus of polynesian araneomorph spiders. the majority of these spiders are found in new zealand, with a few species also found on the nearby islands of tonga and samoa. the genus was first described by simon, 1878. the genus is characterised by having a large head and thorax, comparatively short legs, and a long abdomen. the eyes are large and the male has eight spinnerets. the females have six to eight spinnerets, as well as smaller ovipositors. the spiders are brown to black, with yellow or white markings on the abdomen and legs. they live in lowland
voss v. fisher, 113 u.s. 213 (1885), was a united states supreme court case that determined the meaning of the maritime term "high seas." the case arose from a dispute between the owners of two steamboats, the voss and the fisher, over which vessel had authority to navigate the high seas. the voss was registered in milwaukee, wisconsin, but the fisher was registered in new york city. the fisher argued that it had authority because it was registered in a port city. the voss argued that it had authority because it was registered in a state with an admiralty court.
